title: Fresno County Land Patents pre-1892
name: Fresno County Land Patents pre-1892
description:
This file contains all land patents that were filed with the State of California in historic Fresno County before 1892. It includes information on the date the patent was filed, the name of the person who filed it, how the patent was paid for, and the size and location of each patent.
For further analyses and commentary, please read Cameron Ormsby's article "Land Speculation in Fresno County: 1860-1891" on the Spatial History Project website.
Sources: Fresno County Atlas (1891) created by Thomas H. Thompson, Land Patent Database from State of California
Credits:
The study was conducted at Stanford's Spatial History Lab (spatialhistory.stanford.edu). The research was made possible through funding provided by NSF Award 0820501, Mellon Distinguished Professor Grant (Richard White), and the Vice Provost for Undergraduate Education at Stanford. Historical research and digitization completed by Cameron Ormsby (cormsby@stanford.edu) in Summer 2010. Technical support and project management by Erik Steiner (ebs110@stanford.edu). Additional support provided by Kathy Harris, Jake Coolidge, Killeen Hanson, Evgenia Schneider, and Daniel Meyer. 
Access and use limitations:
The reuse and adaptation of this data is encouraged for scholarly work. Its commercial use is strictly prohibited. Kindly inform the authors of any adaptations or modifications made to improve the quality of the data.
